  "affected": [
    "kubernetes:kubelet <= v1.28.0",
    "kubernetes:kubelet <= v1.27.4",
    "kubernetes:kubelet <= v1.26.7",
    "kubernetes:kubelet <= v1.25.12",
    "kubernetes:kubelet <= v1.24.16",
    "kubernetes:### How do I mitigate this vulnerability?",
    "kubernetes:The provided patch fully mitigates the vulnerability (see fix impact below).  Full mitigation for this class of issues requires patches applied for CVE-2023-3676, CVE-2023-3955, and CVE-2023-3893.",
    "kubernetes:Outside of applying the provided patch, there are no known mitigations to this vulnerability.",
    "kubernetes:#### Fixed Versions",
    "kubernetes:kubelet master - fixed by #120128",
    "kubernetes:kubelet v1.28.1 - fixed by #120134",
    "kubernetes:kubelet v1.27.5 - fixed by #120135",
    "kubernetes:kubelet v1.26.8 - fixed by #120136",
    "kubernetes:kubelet v1.25.13 - fixed by #120137",
    "kubernetes:kubelet v1.24.17 - fixed by #120138",
    "kubernetes:Fix impact:** Passing Windows Powershell disk format options to in-tree volume plugins will result in an error during volume provisioning on the node.  There are no known use cases for this functionality, nor is this functionality supported by any known out-of-tree CSI driver.",
    "kubernetes:To upgrade, refer to the documentation:",
    "kubernetes:https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/cluster-upgrade/",
    "kubernetes:### Detection",
    "kubernetes:Kubernetes audit logs can be used to detect if this vulnerability is being exploited. Pod create events with embedded powershell commands are a strong indication of exploitation.",
    "kubernetes:If you find evidence that this vulnerability has been exploited, please contact security@kubernetes.io",
    "kubernetes:#### Acknowledgements",
    "kubernetes:This vulnerability was discovered by James Sturtevant @jsturtevant and Mark Rossetti @marosset during the process of fixing CVE-2023-3676 (that original CVE was reported by Tomer Peled @tomerpeled92)",
    "kubernetes:The issue was fixed and coordinated by the fix team:",
    "kubernetes:James Sturtevant @jsturtevant",
    "kubernetes:Mark Rossetti @marosset",
    "kubernetes:Andy Zhang @andyzhangx",
    "kubernetes:Justin Terry @jterry75",
    "kubernetes:Kulwant Singh @KlwntSingh",
    "kubernetes:Micah Hausler @micahhausler",
    "kubernetes:Rita Zhang @ritazh",
    "kubernetes:and release managers:",
    "kubernetes:Jeremy Rickard @jeremyrickard",
    "kubernetes:kubernetes-csi-proxy <= v2.0.0-alpha.0",
    "kubernetes:kubernetes-csi-proxy <= v1.1.2",
    "kubernetes:The provided patch fully mitigates the vulnerability and has no known side effects.  Full mitigation for this class of issues requires patches applied for CVE-2023-3676, CVE-2023-3955, and CVE-2023-3893.",
    "kubernetes:kubernetes-csi-proxy master - fixed by https://github.com/kubernetes-csi/csi-proxy/pull/306",
    "kubernetes:kubernetes-csi-proxy v2.0.0-alpha.1 - fixed by https://github.com/kubernetes-csi/csi-proxy/pull/307",
    "kubernetes:kubernetes-csi-proxy v1.1.3 - fixed by https://github.com/kubernetes-csi/csi-proxy/pull/306",
    "kubernetes:To upgrade: cordon the node, stop the associated Windows service, replace the csi-proxy.exe binary, restart the associated Windows service, and un-cordon the node.  See the installation docs for more details: https://github.com/kubernetes-csi/csi-proxy#installation",
    "kubernetes:If a Windows host process daemon set is used to run kubernetes-csi-proxy such as https://github.com/kubernetes-csi/csi-driver-smb/blob/master/charts/latest/csi-driver-smb/templates/csi-proxy-windows.yaml, simply upgrade the image to a fixed version such as ghcr.io/kubernetes-sigs/sig-windows/csi-proxy:v1.1.3",
    "kubernetes:Mauricio Poppe @mauriciopoppe"
  ],
